1
00:00:00,995 --> 00:00:09,763
In this video we will see how to enter course.We click on the e-learning platform menu item.

2
00:00:12,514 --> 00:00:16,450
If you are not logged in you will be redirected to the log in form.

3
00:00:16,717 --> 00:00:20,593
We enter our data and click the login button.

4
00:00:32,648 --> 00:00:36,976
The list with the courses you are registered to is displayed.

5
00:00:37,073 --> 00:00:39,689
To enter a course just click on it.

6
00:00:42,726 --> 00:00:48,664
This is the main page of the course, and these are the available features of the course.

7
00:00:49,766 --> 00:01:00,952
Online tests and excersises, announcements about the course, assignments, online notebook, and the course content.

8
00:01:02,105 --> 00:01:05,345
We click on this icon to access the videos.

9
00:01:10,052 --> 00:01:14,244
From the list on the left you can select the content you want to view.

10
00:01:14,999 --> 00:01:23,140
The main types of content are the videos, the pdf notes, and self assessment questions for the corresponding video.

11
00:01:24,204 --> 00:01:30,858
The green ticks on the right of the title means that you have visited this link but not necessarily seen the content.

12
00:01:31,757 --> 00:01:35,477
Now we click on the play button to start the video.

13
00:02:01,964 --> 00:02:05,116
These are the options we have for the video.

14
00:02:05,515 --> 00:02:08,321
We can move the playbar to the minute we want.

15
00:02:13,021 --> 00:02:16,047
And from here can choose the quality of the video.

16
00:02:16,795 --> 00:02:21,338
For slow internet connections, it is better to choose the lower quality.

17
00:02:25,878 --> 00:02:31,822
By clicking this button, we can switch the subtitles to another language or disable them.

18
00:02:35,611 --> 00:02:39,669
We can also edit the sound and set video on fullscreen mode.

19
00:02:43,439 --> 00:02:50,431
Please make sure that you are using the pause button, which is excactly below the video player together with another resume button

20
00:02:50,778 --> 00:02:54,594
instead of the pause button at the bottom left of the video player.

21
00:03:00,307 --> 00:03:02,914
Here we can keep notes for the video.

22
00:03:07,314 --> 00:03:11,829
Click the "Save my notes" button to save them before leaving the page.

23
00:03:25,378 --> 00:03:31,754
Depending on the module, theory or materia medica, you can find more information or references below the player.

24
00:03:32,209 --> 00:03:36,953
For example the other books, that you need to study along side with the video.

25
00:03:42,437 --> 00:03:45,637
Below each video link there are notes in pdf format.

26
00:03:50,888 --> 00:03:54,648
You can either download them on your device by clicking this button,

27
00:03:55,989 --> 00:03:58,357
or print them by clicking this button

28
00:03:59,488 --> 00:04:05,791
If you can't view the pdf notes, please make sure you have a pdf reader installed on your device.

29
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:17,469
The self assessment questions are questions about the corresponding video and help you assess if your have understood the content.

30
00:04:18,422 --> 00:04:24,364
Read the question and try to answer it then click the show answer link to confirm your answer.

31
00:04:38,240 --> 00:04:42,098
We click the "Course home" link to go back to courses main page.

32
00:04:45,562 --> 00:04:49,723
Here is another way to keep notes for the course.

33
00:04:51,913 --> 00:04:55,809
As you can see here are the notes we kept for the video.

34
00:04:56,523 --> 00:05:00,211
We can edit or export them to pdf format.

35
00:05:08,481 --> 00:05:11,730
We can also create new notes by clicking here.

36
00:05:15,309 --> 00:05:21,822
In the next video you will see how to enter an online test, and how to submit your assignments and tests.

